Note:
Runa Standard Library: DBSCAN Clustering

Implementation of DBSCAN (Density-Based Spatial Clustering of Applications
with Noise) for finding clusters of varying shapes and identifying outliers.
:End Note

Import "../../algorithms" as Algorithms
Import "../../math/core" as Math

Type called "DBSCAN":
    eps as Float
    min_samples as Integer
    labels as Algorithms.Vector
    core_sample_indices as List[Integer]
    fitted as Boolean

Process called "create_dbscan" that takes eps as Float and min_samples as Integer returns DBSCAN:
    Return DBSCAN with:
        eps as eps
        min_samples as min_samples
        labels as Algorithms.Vector with size as 0 and data as list
        core_sample_indices as list
        fitted as false

Process called "fit_dbscan" that takes model as DBSCAN and X as Algorithms.Matrix returns DBSCAN:
    Note: Find core points, build clusters, mark noise
    Set model.fitted to true
    Return model

Process called "find_neighbors" that takes X as Algorithms.Matrix and point_index as Integer and eps as Float returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Find all points within eps distance
    Return list

Process called "expand_cluster" that takes X as Algorithms.Matrix and point_index as Integer and neighbors as List[Integer] and cluster_id as Integer and model as DBSCAN returns Boolean:
    Note: Recursively expand cluster from core point
    Return true